node.title: Ancient giant "sea dragon" fossil discovered in U.K.
node.description: The fossil is nearly 33 feet long — roughly the size of a bus — and is believed to be the largest ichthyosaur skeleton ever discovered in the U.K.

node.title: Space heater blamed for deadly NYC fire: "Kids fighting for their life"
node.description: Officials blamed a malfunctioning space heater for the fire, which also injured dozens of residents in the Bronx on Sunday morning.

node.title: Service members, families affected by toxic water at base seek justice
node.description: The bipartisan Camp Lejeune Justice Act would address what senators call unfair legal barriers blocking military families from suing the government.

node.title: Michaela Jae Rodriguez and "Squid Game" star make history at Globes
node.description: Without a live television or streaming event, the Golden Globes were quieter than usual this year, but some stars still made history at the awards ceremony.

node.title: Why more Americans than ever are quitting their jobs
node.description: The United States is seeing its highest "quit rate" since the government started keeping track two decades ago. Bill Whitaker speaks with employers who are scrambling to find help and people who left their jobs and aren't looking back.

node.title: Notable Deaths in 2022
node.description: A look back at the esteemed personalities who've left us this year, who'd touched us with their innovation, creativity and humanity.

node.title: As the U.S. and Russia talk, Ukraine braces for another invasion
node.description: A Ukrainian commander battling Russian-backed rebels tells CBS News they're "ready for battle," as Putin's posturing brings echoes of the Cold War.

node.title: One of Bob Saget's final posts was musing on Betty White, afterlife
node.description: Bob Saget died just a little more than a week after Betty White, whom he called "a remarkable talent and human being."

node.title: Pete Davidson remembers Bob Saget's help and friendship
node.description: Davidson, who famously stays off social media, shared a message via his friend's Instagram.

node.title: GOP Congressman Jim Jordan won't cooperate with January 6 committee
node.description: Jordan said the committee's request is an "unprecedented and inappropriate demand."

node.title: 6 New California Laws You Should Know About
node.description: Changes to the minimum wage, composting rules, police procedures and more.

node.title: Take-Two Interactive buys Zynga in $12.7 billion deal
node.description: Shares of Zynga, the company behind FarmVille and Words With Friends, surge more than 50% after blockbuster purchase.

node.title: Alec Baldwin insists he is complying with cell phone search warrant
node.description: "Any suggestion that I am not complying with requests or orders or demands or search warrants about my phone, that's bulls***, that's a lie" the actor said.

node.title: Dramatic video captures cliff collapsing on tourist boats, killing 10
node.description: One video, shared on social media, showed the minute before the incident, with people warning that "lots of stones are falling."

node.title: Amy Schneider becomes first woman to win over $1 million on "Jeopardy!"
node.description: Schneider is one of only four people to have ever broken the $1 million mark on the quiz show in regular-season play.

node.title: Model says a stranger used an Apple AirTag to track her
node.description: In a series of videos posted to her Instagram stories, Nader called it the "scariest experience."

node.title: Police pull injured pilot from plane moments before train crash
node.description: The plane had landed on the tracks at a railroad crossing, and officers were on the scene almost immediately.

node.title: Transcript: Speaker Nancy Pelosi on "Face the Nation"
node.description: The following is a transcript of an interview with House Speaker Nancy Pelosi that aired Sunday, January 9, 2022, on "Face the Nation."

node.title: 19 dead, including 9 children, in "horrific" New York City fire
node.description: The fire appears to have been started by an portable space heater, New York City Fire Commissioner Daniel Nigro said.

node.title: Pelosi: "There's an agreement to be reached" with Manchin
node.description: Senator Joe Manchin pulled his support for Mr. Biden's $1.75 trillion social spending plan last month.

node.title: Bob Saget, comedian and "Full House" star, has died at 65
node.description: A cause of death was not immediately announced.

node.title: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez tests positive for COVID-19
node.description: "She is experiencing symptoms and recovering at home," her office said in a statement on Sunday.

node.title: Australian court reinstates Djokovic's visa, but he may lose it again
node.description: The decision apparently renews his chance to win a record 21st Grand Slam title at the upcoming Australian Open. The visa was canceled last week because he's unvaccinated.

node.title: How historians view Trump – and how Trump sees himself
node.description: A panel of historians is releasing its third collection of essays assessing the accomplishments and failures of a presidential administration – and for the first time, a former president spoke to the group to offer his own take on his time in office.

node.title: Co-stars, friends react to Bob Saget's death: "Utter shock"
node.description: "I am broken. I am gutted," Saget's "Full House" co-star John Stamos said. "I will never have another friend like him."

node.title: Past 7 years are hottest on record "by a clear margin," scientists say
node.description: 2021 continued the trend as one of the hottest years on record since the 1800s.

node.title: 27 rescued from ice chunk floating off Green Bay
node.description: No one was hurt. One witness said the crack in the ice ran as far as the eye could see. Most of the rescued had been ice fishing.

node.title: More women slain by "shopping cart killer" ID'd as cops seek more victims
node.description: Police have scanned through all of the "missing person cases" from 35 police departments to find more victims.

node.title: Yanks reportedly set to name MLB minor leagues' first woman manager
node.description: The Yanks are expected to name Rachel Balkovec as the new manager of their Low-A affiliate, the Tampa Tarpons. She'd be be the first woman to manage on a full-time basis in MLB's version of the minor leagues.

node.title: Skier missing Christmas found dead near California resort
node.description: Search-and-rescue volunteers discovered the body of Rory Angelotta roughly 3 miles from the boundaries of the ski resort.
